{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d76c9ea728f90fa031", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "114", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A magnetic dipole is under the influence of two magnetic fields. The angle between the field directions is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo></math> and one of the fields has a magnitude of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>. If the dipole comes to stable equilibrium at an angle of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo></math> with this field, what is the magnitude of the other field?", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "rvYKb", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 149px; top: -5.77778px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 149px; top: -5.77778px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "7IjRa", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 149px; top: -5.77778px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "5KYxq", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "3Hpt7", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 149px; top: -5.77778px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Let one of the magnetic fields is B<sub>1</sub> and other is B<sub>2</sub>. Angle between B<sub>1</sub> and B<sub>2</sub> is 60<sup>o</sup>.<br /><br />Given,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B<sub>1</sub> = 1.2 x 10<sup>-2</sup> T<br /><br />Dipole is in equilibrium at an angle 15<sup>o</sup> from B<sub>1</sub> or 60<sup>o</sup> - 15<sup>o</sup> = 45<sup>o</sup> from B<sub>2</sub><br /><br />Torque on dipole due to magnetic field B<sub>1</sub><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <math> <mrow> <msub> <mi>\u03c4</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>M</mtext> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <msub> <mtext>B</mtext> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mtext>&nbsp;sin</mtext> <mn>&nbsp;1</mn> <msup> <mn>5</mn> <mtext>o</mtext> </msup> </mrow> </math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;......(i)<br /><br /><span style=\"line-height: 1.6em;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/neet/images/EM0015388_AnsExp_1_1.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%; object-fit:contain\" style=\"line-height: 1.6em; width: 175px; height: 146px;\" /><br /><br /><span style=\"line-height: 1.6em;\">where, </span>M<span style=\"line-height: 1.6em;\"> is the magnetic moment. Torque on dipole due to magnetic field </span>B<sub>2</sub><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <math> <mrow> <msub> <mi>\u03c4</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>M</mtext> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <msub> <mtext>B</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mtext>&nbsp;sin</mtext> <mn>&nbsp;4</mn> <msup> <mn>5</mn> <mtext>o</mtext> </msup> </mrow> </math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; .....(ii)<br /><br />As dipole is in the equilibrium, then<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <msub> <mi>\u03c4</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <msub> <mi>\u03c4</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; M X B<sub>1</sub> sin 15<sup>o</sup> = M x B<sub>2</sub> sin 45<sup>o</sup>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; [From Eqs. (i) and (ii)]<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <math> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mtext>.</mtext> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mn>1</mn> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </msup> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mtext>sin&nbsp;</mtext> <mn>1</mn> <msup> <mn>5</mn> <mtext>o</mtext> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>sin&nbsp;</mtext> <mn>4</mn> <msup> <mn>5</mn> <mtext>o</mtext> </msup> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <msub> <mtext>B</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <math> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>B</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mtext>.</mtext> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mn>1</mn> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </msup> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mtext>.</mtext> <mn>2</mn> <mn>5</mn> <mn>8</mn> <mn>8</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mtext>.</mtext> <mn>7</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>7</mn> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mn>4</mn> <mtext>.</mtext> <mn>4</mn> <mo>\u00d7</mo> <mn>1</mn> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> </msup> <mtext>&nbsp;T</mtext> </mrow> </math><br /><br />Thus, the magnitude of the other field is 4.4. x 10<sup>-3</sup> T.", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61602420ae6dd863a9d1d7d8", "6160241f1a832a8dea12fbf0", "616024236098c3dc0cc3e764", "61602422b42cfaef18219875", "616024227e2ba4496fdd4552", "61964c8c8d7ade9f02022966", "61c08987636555dc34527e11", "61e7bd70643383b6c26bfb1d", "61964c8e8811f774a40dd9f1", "62962123b040395dcc21a751", "629f3a9143c2c00ea1d2f857", "629109edc3391b7808eb05af", "61bb820fdb486fa25580e4bd", "629f390c27047111eccefe03", "64eb06c03118f713ecfef077", "66d5853aa75f05ee8564f568", "67921d601d5b5072da5e9a88", "67fdff4f378e1624ea7b6a03", "6809202a3a10446a207fded7"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}}